sql:
SELECT c.customer_id, c.first_name, c.last_name
FROM customers c
WHERE c.customer_id IN (
    SELECT o.customer_id
    FROM orders o
    WHERE o.order_id IN (
        SELECT i.order_id
        FROM order_items i
        WHERE i.total_price = (
            SELECT MAX(total_price) FROM order_items
        )
    )
);

external_knowledge:
- 'travelers' refers to 'customers';
- 'guides' refers to 'sales representatives';
- 'journey of phone calls' refers to interactions where the type of interaction was 'phone call';
- 'treasures' refers to 'products' ordered by customers.
